column4: <content>[recto] P.B. II L'avocat des mauvaises choses. [Georges] MARLIER, Erasme et la peinture flamande de son temps, Damme [Musée van Maerlant] 1954, citaat p. 263 (pl. 45); [verso] [toegevoegde vermelding]: 'F.G. Hulin is probably right, but there are strong elements of P.B.I in this composition: The very bold foreshortening of the woman, the composition in the whole agrees with composition like Doyen de Renaix (1556-57), Witch of Malleghem 1559, Alchemist 1558). It is the composition of an unknown artist, hardly P.B. II who was inspired by these works of P.B.I. The raggeduess in the clothes also in the 'works of Mercy' based on B's engraving.'</content>
